        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 5:39PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 539 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fairview, or 8 miles south of Kingston, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Oak Ridge, Lenoir City, Kingston, Loudon, Fairview, Philadelphia,
Paint Rock, Bradbury, and Tellico Village.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
